-- New York City Temperature Hits 103, Breaking Record for Day by 2 Degrees
-- Brian K. Sullivan
-- 2010-07-06T20:13:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/new-york-city-temperature-hits-103-breaking-record-for-day-by-2-degrees.html

          
          
             The temperature in New York City hit
103 degrees in Central Park as of 3 p.m., breaking the record
for the date by two degrees, Richard Castro of the National
Weather Service said in an interview with Bloomberg News.  
